LAGOS – Following his victory at the All Progressives Congress’, APC primaries held earlier today, Lagos State Governor, Mr. Babajide Olusola Sanwo-Olu has expressed profound gratitude to all the delegates who aided him in securing victory. He also thanked the leadership of the party for giving him the opportunity at another chance to steer the reins of the state under the party’s flag. “I am grateful to God, the distinguished delegates and the leadership of the APC for the chance to continue the good work of governance that we have begun in our great state.” -Advertisement- “With this resounding victory in the primary election, I am confident that we are united and ready to continue to be a beacon of hope and service to this great state. To the other contestants, I congratulate you for being a part of this very democratic process and invite you to join hands with me #ForAGreaterLagos“, he wrote on his official twitter page, @jidesanwoolu. See tweets below;